This paper discusses the complexity analysis of reasoning problems for description logics, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper specifically focuses on the framework of parameterized complexity theory, which is relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses case studies related to concept satisfiability and TBoxes, which are topics commonly studied in the subfield of description logics (cs.DL).
